# SSRF Prevention

Source: cursor-security-rules. Applies to all code that performs outbound HTTP/network requests.

## 1. No User-Controlled Target URLs
- Never use raw or unchecked user input as the destination for outbound requests.
- **Unsafe:** `requests.get(request.args["url"])`

## 2. Block Private/Internal IP Ranges
- Do not allow requests to localhost, 127.0.0.1, 169.254.0.0/16, 192.168.0.0/16, 10.0.0.0/8, or other internal/reserved ranges.

## 3. Resolve and Validate Hostnames
- Perform DNS resolution and validate that the resolved IP is in an allowed range before connecting.

## 4. Restrict Protocols and Ports
- Allow only HTTP/HTTPS and known-safe ports (e.g. 80, 443). Block file:, gopher, FTP, or custom handlers.

## 5. Do Not Forward Auth Headers Automatically
- Never pass internal tokens, cookies, or auth headers when proxying/forwarding outbound requests unless explicitly scoped and audited.
